Here's a MAUI `CollectionView` with single selection and pull-to-refresh:

## XAML

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ItemsPage">

    <RefreshView Command="{Binding RefreshCommand}"
                 IsRefreshing="{Binding IsRefreshing}">

        <CollectionView ItemsSource="{Binding Items}"
                        SelectionMode="Single"
                        SelectedItem="{Binding SelectedItem}"
                        SelectionChangedCommand="{Binding ItemSelectedCommand}">
            <CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
                <DataTemplate>
                    <Grid Padding="10">
                        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="16" />
                    </Grid>
                </DataTemplate>
            </CollectionView.ItemTemplate>
        </CollectionView>

    </RefreshView>
</ContentPage>
```

## ViewModel Bindings Explained

| Binding | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `Items` | `ObservableCollection<T>` powering the list |
| `IsRefreshing` | `bool` property — set `false` when refresh completes |
| `RefreshCommand` | `IAsyncRelayCommand` that calls your API and repopulates `Items` |
| `SelectedItem` | Two-way bound; holds the tapped item (clear it after navigation to allow re-selection) |
| `ItemSelectedCommand` | Fires on selection change; navigates to detail page |

## ViewModel Skeleton (CommunityToolkit.Mvvm)

```csharp
public partial class ItemsViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    private readonly IApiService _api;
    private readonly INavigationService _nav;

    [ObservableProperty] private bool isRefreshing;
    [ObservableProperty] private ItemModel? selectedItem;

    public ObservableCollection<ItemModel> Items { get; } = new();

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task RefreshAsync()
    {
        var data = await _api.GetItemsAsync();
        Items.Clear();
        foreach (var item in data) Items.Add(item);
        IsRefreshing = false;
    }

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task ItemSelectedAsync()
    {
        if (SelectedItem is null) return;
        await _nav.GoToAsync("DetailPage", SelectedItem);
        SelectedItem = null; // reset so the same item can be re-selected
    }
}
```

**Key points:**

- Wrap `CollectionView` in `RefreshView` — the pull gesture drives `RefreshCommand`.
- Set `SelectedItem = null` after navigation so the user can tap the same row again.
- `SelectionMode="Single"` ensures only one item highlights at a time.
- `IsRefreshing = false` stops the spinner; forgetting this leaves the indicator spinning.
